$a = random(2,10,1);
$b = random(2,10,1);
$c = random(3,8,1);
$b1 = 1/$b;

BEGIN_TEXT

Represent the function \( $a \ln($b-x) \) as a power series (Maclaurin
series) \(\displaystyle  f(x) = \sum_{n=0}^\infty c_n x^n \) $BR

\( c_0 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_1 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_2 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_3 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

\( c_4 = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  $BR

Find the radius of convergence \( R = \) \{ans_rule(20)\}  . $BR

END_TEXT

$ans0 =  $a*ln($b) ;
$ans1 =  (-1)*$a*$b1 ;
$ans2 =  (-1)*$a*($b1 **2)/2;
$ans3 =  (-1)*$a*($b1 **3)/3;
$ans4 =  (-1)*$a*($b1 **4)/4;
$ans5 =  $b;

ANS(num_cmp($ans0));
ANS(num_cmp($ans1));
ANS(num_cmp($ans2));
ANS(num_cmp($ans3));
ANS(num_cmp($ans4));
ANS(num_cmp($ans5));

